---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DroneGallery from '../components/DroneGallery.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Tristan Trébaol">
  <main>
    <!-- ═══════════════════ HEADER ═══════════════════ -->
    <header class="header">
      <h1 class="name">Tristan Trébaol</h1>
      <p>Hi, I'm Tristan. I am interested to develop models that are useful in the real world. I also enjoy building hardware. A few things about me:</p>
    </header>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ MODELLING ═══════════════════ -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <h2>Modelling</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p>
          Lastly, during my PhD at Cambridge I worked on a probabilistic graphical model of lung health to improve life expectancy and wellbeing in cystic fibrosis (<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/u/2/d/1KzY6G1w7RWFxa7MzYBQC_WszzzMhRmTT/view?usp=sharing">manuscript</a>). Whilst doing so I implemented a recursive version of the belief propagation algorithm that was 20x faster than current method on <a href="https://pgmpy.org/_modules/pgmpy/inference/ExactInference.html#BeliefPropagationWithMessagePassing">PGMPY</a>. It's available <a href="https://pgmpy.org/_modules/pgmpy/inference/ExactInference.html#BeliefPropagationWithMessagePassing">here</a>.
        </p>

        <pre><code><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="cls">_RecursiveMessageSchedulingQuery</span>:
<span class="cm">    """Private class used in `BeliefPropagationWithMessagePassing.query()`</span>
<span class="cm">    to efficiently manage the message scheduling across the different</span>
<span class="cm">    queried variables, in a recursive way.</span>
<span class="cm">    """</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          Previously, I did research in geodesic CNN to accelerate industrial R&D, which turned into a startup called <a href="https://www.neuralconcept.com/">Neural Concept</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ WRITING CODE ═══════════════════ -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <h2>Writing code</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p>
          From 2021 to 2022 I was writing code at <a href="https://gitstart.com/">Gitstart</a> (YC19). I journaled <a href="https://www.notion.so/tristantrebaol/Daily-Tristan-4bf8daf9da3b45b89b9145c863ca92c8?source=copy_link">my daily learnings</a> for a year and also shipped <a href="https://www.notion.so/tristantrebaol/Daily-Tristan-4bf8daf9da3b45b89b9145c863ca92c8?source=copy_link#dc2368fef3dd44d4826740b1eab03e6a">open-source contributions</a> in Elixir, Typescript, and Python.
        </p>

        <figure class="photo reveal">
          <img src="/images/gitpraise.png" alt="Gitpraise screenshot" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          I believe that <a href="https://www.notion.so/tristantrebaol/TDD-is-drastically-underrated-0fde747cad4b4a8c9a3b48187192ea92?source=copy_link">TDD is drastically underrated</a>. I also enjoyed reading: <em>The Missing README</em>, <em>The Pragmatic Engineer</em>, <em>Normal Accidents</em>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          I started coding in 2014 when I enrolled for CS50 (Harvard CS) with two high school friends.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ BUILDING HARDWARE ═══════════════════ -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <h2>Building hardware</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p>
          During my masters in computational science, I co-founded a <a href="https://www.epflspacecraftteam.ch/">space mission</a> from my kitchen table in Switzerland. We raised 2.5M CHF from the European Space Agency and launched two satellites in low earth orbit. I spoke about it on <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/06ThLys4c7i8pEowlWxvpR?si=c6652ddb1d0e4131">radio</a>, in an <a href="https://actu.epfl.ch/news/epfl-moves-boldly-into-space-with-its-chess-satell/">article</a>, and on <a href="https://youtu.be/OPOPqDzs0KE?t=133">video</a>. Team's efforts led to <a href="https://www.dphispace.com/">DPhi Space</a> spin-off. We ensure perenity of the project in an association of space enthusiasts which is still active. Next launch planned in October 2026.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          In my EPFL student time, I would spend most of my time at the makerspace. For example, we built the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TFE88LYaePM">first RC bifoiler worldwide</a> (picture below). It was the fastest boat in the circuit history in the international student competition, and I was lucky enough to pilot a few races.
        </p>

        <figure class="photo">
          <img src="/images/bifoiler.png" alt="The RC bifoiler — first of its kind" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          We also built a freight boat prototype that carried 200 kg of weight.
        </p>
        <figure class="photo">
          <img src="/images/freight-boat.png" alt="Freight boat prototype" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          I also assembled a racing quadcopter importing all parts from China. My electronic nerd friend didn't tell me it was super over engineered. I limited it to 1% of the full power and it was finally controllable.
        </p>
        <DroneGallery />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ CYSTIC FIBROSIS ═══════════════════ -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <h2>Challenging myself to support cystic fibrosis</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">with brother and friends</p>

      <ul class="cf-timeline">
        <li class="cf-timeline__item reveal">
          <span class="cf-timeline__year">2023</span>
          <span class="cf-timeline__desc">Half ironman with a group of friends</span>
          <figure class="photo">
            <img src="/images/half-ironman.png" alt="Half ironman group photo" loading="lazy" />
          </figure>
        </li>
        <li class="cf-timeline__item reveal">
          <span class="cf-timeline__year">2021</span>
          <span class="cf-timeline__desc">Swam across Lake Geneva from Lausanne to Evian</span>
          <figure class="photo">
            <img src="/images/lake-leman.jpg" alt="Swimming across Lake Geneva" loading="lazy" />
          </figure>
        </li>
        <li class="cf-timeline__item reveal">
          <span class="cf-timeline__year">2018</span>
          <span class="cf-timeline__desc">Ran an ironman with my brother — second place for my age category</span>
        </li>
        <li class="cf-timeline__item reveal">
          <span class="cf-timeline__year">2015</span>
          <span class="cf-timeline__desc">7th and 9th at Victoria Peak trail with my brother, Hong Kong</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ SAILING ═══════════════════ -->
    <section class="section reveal">
      <h2>Sailing</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <p>
          I grew up in Brittany, France, where I spent my free time sailing competitively. By the time I was 15, I had accumulated 10,000 hours which led me to win two world championship titles with my brother in pre-olympic series (<a href="https://www.ouest-france.fr/bretagne/vannes-56000/les-freres-trebaol-champions-du-monde-de-catamaran-724483">article</a>).
        </p>

        <figure class="photo">
          <img src="/images/sailing-catamaran.png" alt="Sailing on a foiling catamaran" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block reveal">
        <p>
          In 2015 I was invited to the French chapter of the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SU0NPu0ALFA&pp=ygUoZnJhbmNlIGZpbmFsZSByZWRidWxsIGZvaWxpbmcgZ2VuZXJhdGlvbtIHCQnZCgGHKiGM7w%3D%3D">Red Bull Foiling Generation</a>. It taught me <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Baj4WSFOm4">the hard way</a> how to sail on foiling catamaran. I then joined Realteam, Tixwave and raced against Alinghi in Lake Geneva on ETF26 and 69F, coached and skippered the Cambridge crew in the UK university nationals.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════ FOOTER ═══════════════════ -->
    <footer class="footer reveal">
      <div class="footer__cta">say hi</div>
      <nav class="footer__links">
        <a href="mailto:tristan@trebaol.com">tristan@trebaol.com</a>
        <span class="footer__dot">&middot;</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/tristantreb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github</a>
        <span class="footer__dot">&middot;</span>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tristan-trebaol/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">linkedin</a>
      </nav>
    </footer>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-sm) var(--space-xl);
  }

  /* ── Header ── */
  .header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  /* ── Sections ── */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-card-border);
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-top: calc(var(--space-md) * -1);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }

  .content-block {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .content-block:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Photos ── */
  .photo {
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-card-border);
  }

  .photo img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── CF Timeline ── */
  .cf-timeline {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .cf-timeline__item {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0 var(--space-sm);
  }

  .cf-timeline__year {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    min-width: 3.5em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .cf-timeline__desc {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
  }

  .cf-timeline__item .photo {
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  /* ── Footer ── */
  .footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0 var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-card-border);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .footer__cta {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .footer__links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5em;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .footer__links a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .footer__links a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .footer__dot {
    color: var(--color-text-lighter);
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    main {
      padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-xs) var(--space-lg);
    }

    .header {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .name {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .cf-timeline__item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.15em;
    }

    .cf-timeline__year {
      min-width: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
